PN,39602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1782505102
OL,3,CGrandmother saw bruise on toddler's
OL,4,Cback days before death, murder trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FHer mother, Alexandra Walker, 25, and
OL,8,FHarrison Simpson, 22, deny murder,
OL,9,Fallowing the death of a child, sexual
OL,10,Fassault and child cruelty.
OL,12,FJurors at Teesside Crown Court on
OL,13,FThursday (25 June) were played an
OL,14,Finterview maternal grandmother Claire
OL,15,FWalker gave to detectives following
OL,16,FIsabelle's death in September.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1782505102
OL,3,CGrandmother saw bruise on toddler's
OL,4,Cback days before death, murder trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FShe told police the toddler was chatty
OL,8,Fand intelligent and had generally been
OL,9,Fin good health up to her sustaining a
OL,10,Fbroken leg for which she received
OL,11,Fhospital treatment.
OL,13,FJurors have been told this was 11 days
OL,14,Fbefore she sustained a fatal head
OL,15,Finjury.
OL,17,FAfter the mother and toddler were
OL,18,Fallowed home from hospital, the
OL,19,Fgrandmother visited them and spotted a
OL,20,Fbruise on Isabelle's back.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1782505102
OL,3,CGrandmother saw bruise on toddler's
OL,4,Cback days before death, murder trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FShe told detectives she said "what the
OL,8,Fhell" when she saw it.
OL,10,FMs Walker told police her daughter
OL,11,Fexplained that Isabelle had bumped her
OL,12,Fhead on the settee.
OL,14,FShe told police she thought Isabelle
OL,15,Fhad picked up a virus from hospital
OL,16,Fwhich explained why she looked unwell.
OL,26,@oD@^OUpD@EO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1782505102
OL,3,CGrandmother saw bruise on toddler's
OL,4,Cback days before death, murder trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe grandmother also gave evidence in
OL,8,Fcourt from behind a screen and told
OL,9,FMark McKone KC, representing her
OL,10,Fdaughter, that she had never met
OL,11,FSimpson, who had been dating Walker
OL,12,Ffor some months.
OL,14,FMs Walker told the court her daughter
OL,15,Fexplained that Simpson "had anxiety
OL,16,Fand didn't want to meet with me".
OL,18,FShe said her daughter had been a
OL,19,Fvictim of domestic abuse in the past
OL,20,Fand that was why she had CCTV cameras
OL,21,Fin her home.
OL,26,@wD@XOUxD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1782505102
OL,3,CGrandmother saw bruise on toddler's
OL,4,Cback days before death, murder trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FShe had never seen her daughter hit
OL,8,FIsabelle, and commented her
OL,9,Fgranddaughter was "always immaculately
OL,10,Fdressed" and the house was always
OL,11,Fclean.
OL,13,FAsked by Mr McKone if her daughter
OL,14,Floved Isabelle, Ms Walker replied: "I
OL,15,Fthink she did."
OL,17,FMeanwhile the court also heard from
OL,18,FWalker's stepfather Daniel Ackroyd.
OL,26,@qD@SOUrD@HO]vD@dOUwD@OO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1782505102
OL,3,CGrandmother saw bruise on toddler's
OL,4,Cback days before death, murder trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe jury was told police Mr Ackroyd
OL,8,Freceived a panicked phone call from
OL,9,FWalker after Isabelle collapsed.
OL,11,FHe rushed to the house and performed
OL,12,Ffirst aid on the toddler until
OL,13,Fparamedics arrived, jurors were told.
OL,15,FIn court, Mr McKone asked: "Do you
OL,16,Fagree Alex worshipped Isabelle?"
OL,18,FMr Ackroyd said: "I do agree with
OL,19,Fthat."
OL,26,@wD@\OUxD@`O]zD@ROU{D@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNE Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1782505102
OL,3,CGrandmother saw bruise on toddler's
OL,4,Cback days before death, murder trial
OL,5,Ctold
OL,7,FThe stepfather said Walker was
OL,8,F"visibly shaking" when he arrived, and
OL,9,Fhe dropped to the floor to help
OL,10,FIsabelle.
OL,12,FMr McKone asked: "Was Alex very
OL,13,Fdistressed?"
OL,15,FMr Ackroyd said: "Yes sir, very."
OL,17,FWalker and Simpson deny all charges
OL,18,Fand the trial continues.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@QO]tD@ROUuD@LO]wD@ROUwD@aO]
